reviews.review: An utter disappointment, it has lazy writing and tries to hard to please the crowd.

This movie makes no sense. The force awakens was nostalgic yes but set up a new trilogy with new characters. The last jedi dared to do something different and go in a different direction and take star wars somewhere new. This film undermines all of that. Rather than give the film a proper review, here are the questions I'm left with...

How did palpatine return?
Where did he get all those ships, and who is manning them?
Why, in 8 previous films did everyone fail to mention he had a wife or kids? You'd think that would be important.
Why did kylo and ren kiss?
If Palpatine's plan was to get to Rey all along why did he bother with Kylo? 
When could jedi start force healing?
Why had they built up the character of Rose in the last film to give her two minutes of screen time in this one?
Why did they introduce 3 new characters in the final film of the saga? One who literally doesn't even take her helmet off?
Why did they make such a big deal of C3po losing his memory to instantly get it back?
Why did they make a big point of Chewie dying to reveal instantly he hadn't?
Why was General Hux a mole?
Why was the entire plot like the side quest of a video game?
How come after getting chased by storm troopers the landed exactly on the planet where the dagger was they were looking for?
How did they know EXACTLY where to stand with the dagger?
How did Maz get Lukes saber?

I understand some films have flaws but the sheer number of unanswered questions. This film has just ruined the whole trilogy for me. I never thought I'd say this but, bring back Lucas!
Excellent way to end the most recent three, but felt a bit loose in its connection to the other 6.

It is like they tried to cram 3 movies into 2 hours, and was there even a story? It just jumped from scene to scene with nothing really binding them together. I didn't think they could do worse than Rogue One or The Last Jedi -- but they managed it handily.
This movie is made perfectly it explains everything and is a very fitting end to a classic saga
A deserved final for the saga
Myself and my son loved it! No it doesn't follow the timeline perfect but it was entertaining and good cgi. Definitely must see

I liked how the various story lines were pulled together in the final movie. Placing the Princess in the story was important for her passion and optimism for the rebellion and that she was Ben's mother. Rey returning to Luke's childhood home brings us full circle.
